
[Williamsburg] 30 June 1777. George Wythe, Speaker of the House of Delegates, directs Martin Key, Sheriff of Fluvanna co., to summon [25] freeholders on some convenient day to elect two of the most able and discreet men of the county and to notify the elected delegates to attend legislature at Williamsburg in October to consult of such things as may be for the glory of God, and for the honour and prosperity of the commonwealth.
